### Simple Quiz API Test Requests
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or copy to Postman/Thunder Client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Get API Documentation
GET {{baseUrl}}

### 2. Create a Quiz
POST {{baseUrl}}/quizzes
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Geography Quiz",
  "description": "Test your knowledge of world geography and capitals"
}

### 3. Create Questions (individually)
POST {{baseUrl}}/questions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "What is the capital of France?",
  "options": ["London", "Paris", "Berlin", "Madrid"],
  "keywords": ["capital", "france", "europe"],
  "correctAnswerIndex": 1
}

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/questions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "What is the capital of Japan?",
  "options": ["Seoul", "Beijing", "Tokyo", "Bangkok"],
  "keywords": ["capital", "japan", "asia"],
  "correctAnswerIndex": 2
}

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/questions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "What is the capital of Italy?",
  "options": ["Rome", "Milan", "Venice", "Florence"],
  "keywords": ["capital", "italy", "europe"],
  "correctAnswerIndex": 0
}

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/questions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "Which is the largest ocean?",
  "options": ["Atlantic", "Indian", "Arctic", "Pacific"],
  "keywords": ["ocean", "geography"],
  "correctAnswerIndex": 3
}

### 4. Get all Questions
GET {{baseUrl}}/questions

### 5. Get all Quizzes (with populated questions)
GET {{baseUrl}}/quizzes

### 6. Get single Quiz by ID
# Replace {quizId} with actual ID from previous response
GET {{baseUrl}}/quizzes/{quizId}

### 7. Add single question to a quiz
# Replace {quizId} with actual quiz ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/quizzes/{quizId}/question
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "What is the capital of Germany?",
  "options": ["Munich", "Hamburg", "Berlin", "Frankfurt"],
  "keywords": ["capital", "germany", "europe"],
  "correctAnswerIndex": 2
}

### 8. Add multiple questions to a quiz
# Replace {quizId} with actual quiz ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/quizzes/{quizId}/questions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "What is the capital of Spain?",
      "options": ["Barcelona", "Madrid", "Seville", "Valencia"],
      "keywords": ["capital", "spain", "europe"],
      "correctAnswerIndex": 1
    },
    {
      "text": "What is the capital of Canada?",
      "options": ["Toronto", "Vancouver", "Ottawa", "Montreal"],
      "keywords": ["capital", "canada", "north america"],
      "correctAnswerIndex": 2
    },
    {
      "text": "What is the capital of Australia?",
      "options": ["Sydney", "Melbourne", "Canberra", "Brisbane"],
      "keywords": ["capital", "australia", "oceania"],
      "correctAnswerIndex": 2
    }
  ]
}

### 9. Get quiz with questions that have "capital" keyword
# Replace {quizId} with actual quiz ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/quizzes/{quizId}/populate

### 10. Update a Quiz
# Replace {quizId} with actual quiz ID
PUT {{baseUrl}}/quizzes/{quizId}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "World Geography Quiz - Updated",
  "description": "Updated description for geography quiz"
}

### 11. Update a Question
# Replace {questionId} with actual question ID
PUT {{baseUrl}}/questions/{questionId}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "text": "What is the capital of France? (Updated)",
  "options": ["London", "Paris", "Berlin", "Madrid"],
  "keywords": ["capital", "france", "europe", "updated"],
  "correctAnswerIndex": 1
}

### 12. Delete a Question
# Replace {questionId} with actual question ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/questions/{questionId}

### 13. Delete a Quiz
# Replace {quizId} with actual quiz ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/quizzes/{quizId}
